status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"1pok2","text":"Add new collection. Name “16S rRNA Gene Conserved Regions”.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"an0tc","text":"Upload 16S rRNA gene forward and reverse sequences for the sample.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7be85","text":"Select “Unsaved Consensus” window then click “Features” → “Scan Sequence”. “U515” feature should be highlighted in consensus sequence.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a3dd5","text":"The nucleotide positions of the “U515” marker will be given. Select the “from” box in top right corner of window and type in the nucleotide position that is -385 nt from the beginning of the “U515” marker. Select the “to” box in top right corner of window and type in the nucleotide position that is +216 nt from the end of the “U515” marker. A 620 bp consensus sequence should be generated.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c8t82","text":"To check for quality of consensus sequence select “Align Two Sequences” window and look for differences in base calls between forward and reverse sequences within the consensus sequence. Sometimes there will be a mismatch or gap between forward and reverse sequences. To assist in making the right base call at a certain nucleotide position use FinchTV to view chromatograms and determine the right call using the higher-quality base call.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ee9ti","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"1nkh9","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"software","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"can_edit":true,"developer":"Geospiza Research Team","guid":"594BA030777911ED8E53A76AD2415940","id":1535,"link":"https://digitalworldbiology.com/FinchTV","name":"FinchTV","os_name":"macOS","os_version":"","repository":"","version":"1.5.0"}}}}
